.TH "setup_kdump_cmdline" 9 "setup_kdump_cmdline" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
setup_kdump_cmdline \- Prepend "elfcorehdr=<addr> " to command line of kdump kernel for exporting the core.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "char *" setup_kdump_cmdline
.BI "(struct kimage *image "  ","
.BI "char *cmdline "  ","
.BI "unsigned long cmdline_len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "image" 12
Kexec image
.IP "cmdline" 12
Command line parameters to update.
.IP "cmdline_len" 12
Length of the cmdline parameters.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
kdump segment must be setup before calling this function.

Returns new cmdline buffer for kdump kernel on success, NULL otherwise.
